FBIS4-62334 "drsov094_a_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-094 Daily Report 13 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Deputy Foreign Minister Holds Talks Deputy Foreign Minister Holds Talks LD1305220494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1725 GMT 13 May 94 LD1305220494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Nikolay Geronin] [Text] Moscow, 13 May -- Russia and the DPRK favor boosting bilateral links, including political contacts, Aleksandr Panov, Russian Federation deputy foreign minister, told ITAR-TASS today, after the end of political consultations at the level of deputy heads of foreign departments of Russia and the DPRK. The North Korean side advocated, inter alia, Russia's participation in the Rajin-Sonbong free economic zone, as well as cooperation in Siberia and in the Russian Far East. Both sides stated both countries' economic potential should be put to better use. Moscow and Pyongyang said a new agreement on the participation of the North Korean side in logging in the Russian east should be signed as soon as possible. North Korean workers staying on the Russian territory should abide by the Russian law. Both sides acknowledge the need for creating better living conditions for them, said the Russian deputy foreign minister. The consultations between Aleksandr Panov and his North Korean counterpart Yi In-Kui took place in Moscow on Thursday and Friday.
